Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%grams} to the water and bring back to
the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with
@oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain the @king prawns{300%grams}. Important: Wash your hands and equipment
after handling raw prawns.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the garlic and @cajun spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd
prefer things milder) and fry until fragrant, ~{1%min}.

Once fragrant, stir through the @creme fraiche{150%grams}, @vegetable stock
paste{10%grams}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water for the sauce{100%ml}. Season with
@salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Bring the sauce to a boil, then lower to a simmer until thickened,
~{3-4%mins}.

Stir in the prawns into the pan and cook for another ~{5-6%mins}. Important:
They're cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Once the prawns are cooked, stir through the @peas{120%grams}, cooked pasta and
@butter{20%grams} until the butter has melted, ~{1%min} more.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if you feel it needs it.

Share your Cajun prawn pasta between your bowls. Enjoy!